JOHANNESBURG, February 8 – An 11-year-old boy from Empangeni turned his father’s gun on himself after he fatally shot his 2-year-old sister while playing with the weapon. Police said the tragedy occurred on Saturday at about 23.50 pm. “An 11-year-old boy was playing with his father’s licensed firearm when a shot went off and struck his two-year-old sister. The victim was taken to hospital for medical attention where she later died,” recounted police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbhele. “The brother allegedly turned the gun on himself after seeing what had happened to his sister.” Mbhele said police were investigating a case of murder. An inquest would be held into the deaths. Police urged gun owners to ensure that they safeguard their firearms and warned that failure to do so was a criminal act. – African News Agency (ANA)